TY  - JOUR
AU  - Cooper, Ilan
AU  - Priestley, Richard
T1  - Time-Varying Risk Premiums and the Output Gap
PY  - 2009
Y1  - 2009/07/01
DO  - 10.1093/rfs/hhn087
JO  - The Review of Financial Studies
JA  - Rev Financ Stud
VL  - 22
IS  - 7
SP  - 2801
EP  - 2833
SN  - 0893-9454
AB  - The output gap, a production-based macroeconomic variable, is a strong predictor of U.S. stock returns. It is a prime business cycle indicator that does not include the level of market prices, thus removing any suspicion that returns are forecastable due to a “fad” in prices being washed away. The output gap forecasts returns both in-sample and out-of-sample, and it is robust to a host of checks. We show that the output gap also has predictive power for excess stock returns in other G7 countries and U.S. excess bond returns.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rfs/hhn087
ER  - 



