TY  - JOUR
AU  - Johannes, Michael S.
AU  - Polson, Nicholas G.
AU  - Stroud, Jonathan R.
T1  - Optimal Filtering of Jump Diffusions: Extracting Latent States from Asset Prices
PY  - 2009
Y1  - 2009/07/01
DO  - 10.1093/rfs/hhn110
JO  - The Review of Financial Studies
JA  - Rev Financ Stud
VL  - 22
IS  - 7
SP  - 2759
EP  - 2799
SN  - 0893-9454
AB  - This paper provides an optimal filtering methodology in discretely observed continuous-time jump-diffusion models. Although the filtering problem has received little attention, it is useful for estimating latent states, forecasting volatility and returns, computing model diagnostics such as likelihood ratios, and parameter estimation. Our approach combines time-discretization schemes with Monte Carlo methods. It is quite general, applying in nonlinear and multivariate jump-diffusion models and models with nonanalytic observation equations. We provide a detailed analysis of the filter's performance, and analyze four applications: disentangling jumps from stochastic volatility, forecasting volatility, comparing models via likelihood ratios, and filtering using option prices and returns.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rfs/hhn110
ER  - 



