TY  - JOUR
AU  - Patton, Andrew J.
T1  - Are “Market Neutral” Hedge Funds Really Market Neutral?
PY  - 2009
Y1  - 2009/07/01
DO  - 10.1093/rfs/hhn113
JO  - The Review of Financial Studies
JA  - Rev Financ Stud
VL  - 22
IS  - 7
SP  - 2495
EP  - 2530
SN  - 0893-9454
AB  - Using a variety of different definitions of “neutrality,” this study presents significant evidence against the neutrality to market risk of hedge funds in a range of style categories. I generalize standard definitions of “market neutrality,” and propose five different neutrality concepts. I suggest statistical tests for each neutrality concept, and apply these tests to a database of monthly returns on 1423 hedge funds from five style categories. For the “market neutral” style, approximately one-quarter of the funds exhibit significant exposure to market risk; this proportion is statistically significantly different from zero, but less than the proportion of significant exposures for other hedge fund styles.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rfs/hhn113
ER  - 



